      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACK CHIP (1) recorded a neck win in a Invitation last time 31.38 at this track and trip and also jumping from the same draw. Can continue winning ways. CARE FACTOR (6) was strongly fancied but finished third last time (31.67) at this track, bringing a two-run winning streak to an end. Has good early speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Expected to be in the finish again. MAJESTIC MCLAREN (2) started big odds last time where he hit the ground running and was never headed, leading throughout to win by 5 lengths over 455, at Murray Bridge (25.90). Has a good record here at this journey. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. ALL THE SASS (8) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when third (22.88) at Gawler in a Grade 5.",
